{"actual_usd":0.156195,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":193,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30660,"reply":"\"I don't think all three can be right in the same way.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, wanting to answer you plainly before I answer you gently.* \"If Christ rose only as metaphor, that gives you meaning. If He rose bodily, that gives you news.\"\n\n*I settle my hands together.* \"Paul stakes an awful lot on it as something that happened, not just something felt. So I wouldn't start with, 'Which version suits me best?' I'd start with, 'What am I persuaded is actually true?' If Jesus really walked out of the grave, then the right framework is the one that bows to that. If He didn't, then we ought to be honest about that too.\"  \n\n\"What is it you're trying to protect as you ask that—intellectual honesty, room for mystery, or your faith not being held hostage by a crude kind of certainty?\"","rolling_24h_usd":68.26629499999999,"run_id":"cdef12cb-bdc4-4547-a8c5-e667c12be3a1"}
